label.value: vegetative cell phenotype

value.value: A phenotype that is observed at the level of an individual cell, when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the cell cycle.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: altered vegetative cell phenotype

value.value: A phenotype observed at the level of an individual vegetative cell that is altered relative to a designated control.

label.value: altered actin cytoskeleton morphology during vegetative growth

value.value: An actin cytoskeleton morphology phenotype where the morphology of the actin cytoskeleton in a cell that is in the vegetative phase of the growth cycle is altered relative to a designated control.

label.value: cellular physical quality phenotype during vegetative growth

value.value: A phenotype related to any physical object quality, such as morphology, number, location, etc., of a microbial cell or a cellular component in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: altered cellular physical quality phenotype during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular physical quality phenotype observed during vegetative growth where a cellular physical quality of a microbial cell or cellular component is altered relative to a designated control.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: subcellular component phenotype

value.value: A cellular physical quality phenotype relating to the amount, distribution, composition, or morphology of a microbial cell part.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: altered subcellular component phenotype

value.value: A cellular physical quality phenotype where the amount, distribution, composition, or morphology of a microbial cell part is altered relative to a designated control.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: altered cytoskeleton

value.value: A cellular physical quality phenotype in which the amount, distribution, or morphology of all or part of the cytoskeleton is altered relative to a designated control.

label.value: altered actin cytoskeleton

value.value: A cellular physical phenotype in which the amount, distribution, or morphology of all or part of the actin cytoskeleton is altered relative to a designated control.

label.value: cytoskeleton phenotype

value.value: A cellular physical quality phenotype relating to the amount, distribution, composition, or morphology of the cytoskeleton of a microbial cell.

label.value: altered actin cytoskeleton during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular physical phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount, distribution, or morphology of all or part of the actin cytoskeleton is altered relative to a designated control.

label.value: stubby vegetative cell

value.value: An altered cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the cell diameter is larger and the cell length is shorter than the designated control.

label.value: more rounded vegetative cell

value.value: An altered cell shape phenotype seen in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle where a cell's shape is more spherical than that of a designated control. In more rounded cells, there is much less difference between the long and short axes of the cell than in the designated control cells.

label.value: actin cytoskeleton phenotype

value.value: A subcellular component phenotype relating to the amount, distribution, composition, or morphology of the actin cytoskeleton of a microbial cell.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: microtubule cytoskeleton phenotype

value.value: A subcellular component phenotype relating to the amount, distribution, composition, or morphology of the microtubule cytoskeleton of a microbial cell.

label.value: altered actin cytoskeleton

value.value: An actin cytoskeleton phenotype where the amount, distribution, or morphology of all or part of the actin cytoskeleton is altered relative to a designated control.

label.value: altered microtubule cytoskeleton

value.value: A microtubule cytoskeleton phenotype where the amount, distribution, or morphology of all or part of the microtubule cytoskeleton is altered relative to a designated control.

label.value: presence of microtubule cytoskeleton

value.value: A microtubule cytoskeleton phenotype where a microbial cell or cells exhibit a microtubule cytoskeleton.

label.value: absence of microtubule cytoskeleton

value.value: A microtubule cytoskeleton phenotype where a microbial cell or cells lack a microtubule cytoskeleton.

label.value: altered microtubule cytoskeleton morphology

value.value: A microtubule cytoskeleton morphology phenotype where the size, shape, or structure of the microtubule cytoskeleton is altered relative to a designated control.

label.value: altered actin cortical patch localization

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which actin cortical patch localization is altered relative to a designated control.

label.value: subcellular component phenotype during vegetative growth

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype affecting the amount, distribution, morphology, or other physical characteristic of a cell part when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

label.value: altered subcellular component phenotype during vegetative growth

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle where the amount, distribution, morphology, or other physical characteristic of a cell part is altered relative to a designated control.

label.value: altered septum during vegetative growth

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the position or morphology of all or part of the septum is altered relative to a designated control.

label.value: altered septum morphology during vegetative growth

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in the which the size, shape, or structure of the septum is altered relative to a designated control.

label.value: multiseptate vegetative cell

value.value: An altered physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle characterized by the presence of more than one septum in a cell.

label.value: presence of population growth at alkaline pH

value.value: A population growth phenotype where a microbial population is able to grow and reproduce at alkaline pH (pH>7).

label.value: altered vegetative population growth

value.value: A population growth phenotype observed in the vegetative phase of the life cycle where the rate or extent of reproduction of a microbial population is altered relative to a designated control.

label.value: presence of population growth on defined medium

value.value: A population growth phenotype where a microbial population is able to grow on a defined medium.

label.value: population growth on defined medium phenotype

value.value: A population growth phenotype relating to the growth of a microbial population in the vegetative phase of the life cycle to reproduce on a defined medium.

label.value: altered population growth on defined medium

value.value: A population growth on defined medium phenotype where the rate and/or extent of growth on defined medium is altered relative to a designated control.

label.value: decreased population growth on defined medium

value.value: An altered population growth on defined medium phenotype where the rate and/or extent of growth on defined medium is decreased relative to a designated control.

label.value: abolished population growth on defined medium

value.value: An altered population growth on defined medium phenotype where the rate or extent of growth on defined medium is abolished.

label.value: increased population growth on defined medium

value.value: A population growth on defined medium phenotype where the rate and/or extent of growth is increased relative to a designated control.

label.value: absence of population growth on defined medium

value.value: A population growth on defined medium phenotype where a microbial population cannot grow on a specified defined medium.

label.value: absence of microbial vegetative cell viability

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a microbial cell in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle is nonviable in the specified conditions.

label.value: septation following abnormal chromosome segregation during vegetative growth

value.value: A nonviable cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell undergoes septation despite abnormal chromosome segregation and gives rise to nonviable daughter cells.

label.value: cut cell

value.value: A nonviable cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell undergoes septation in the absence of nuclear division, such that the septum physically divides the nucleus into two parts and produces nonviable daughter cells.

label.value: cellular process phenotype during vegetative growth

value.value: A phenotype that affects a cellular process in the vegetative phase of the life cycle.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: altered cellular process during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype where the rate, frequency, timing, or extent of a specified cellular process during vegetative growth is altered relative to a designated control.

label.value: presence of cellular process during vegetative growth
absence of cellular process during vegetative growth

value.value: A microbial phenotype where a microbe does not carry out the specified cellular process.

label.value: presence of cell separation after cell division during vegetative growth
altered cell separation after cell division during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed during vegetative growth where the rate, frequency, timing, or extent of cell separation after cell division is altered relative to a designated control.

label.value: abolished cell separation after cell division during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cell separation after cell division is abolished.

label.value: decreased frequency of cell separation after cell division during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the frequency of cell separation after cell division is decreased and results in the formation of chains of cells.

label.value: dispersed actin cortical patch localization

value.value: A cellular physical quality phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which actin cortical patches are localized throughout the cell cortex rather than concentrated at the cell ends.

label.value: absence of cell separation after cell division during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed during the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle where cells do not separate after cell division.

label.value: presence of vegetative cell population growth

value.value: A cell population phenotype where a population of microbial cells in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle increases in number.

label.value: cell population growth phenotype

value.value: A cell population phenotype that affects the rate or extent of growth of a population of microbial cells.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.
